content.description: Start with your hands matched on the right side arete and follow it up using a right sloper to get onto the easy side. Really aesthetic arete climb that is on a ridge overlooking the lake. Definitely has been climbed before, but haven't been able to find it in anywhere on MP or a book. If you continue left instead of using the sloper it was definitely harder
content.location: Took a path that trended north east above Railroad Amphitheater. Came across ~200 feet up the ridge. Found between Railroad Amphitheater and Talus field. Probably kind of hard to find since we didn't even really know where we were, but if you come across it, definitely hop on!
